The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, April 30: The department of telecom will shortly convene a meeting with BSNL to take stock of the PSU?s decision on initial public offering. Senior DoT officials said the department wanted to know the reason for an IPO and its timing. However, BSNL has already written to the department of disinvestment that the IPO proposal should not be considered for at least a year. Telecom secretary J.S. Sarma will chair the meeting, which will be attended by BSNL chairman A.K. Sinha and other senior officials.

 Hyderabad, April 30: Denying any conditions attached to loans by the Asian Development Bank, finance minister P Chidambaram today expressed hope that the bank?s funding to India would go up to $2.65 billion by 2008. 

 Mumbai, April 30: The Centre is in talks with five countries, including Qatar, for supplying gas to the Dabhol power project, petroleum secretary M.S. Srinivasan said. Dabhol plant will be generating electricity from its total capacity of 2,015 mw by next year, he added.

 New Delhi, April 30: Ashok Leyland is ?studying several options? for the light commercial vehicles segment, which includes making vehicles ranging between 2.5 and 4 tonnes, said managing director R. Seshasayee.

 Beijing, April 30: For the first time, the Chinese government has allowed the state security fund to invest in foreign markets to expand the resources available for the nation?s growing army of the aged, the state media reported.




